<br>
I strongly suggest dropping Listless Power and Insipid Weakness from your lineup. They just don't have enough effect on mobs to be worth the spell slots, mana useage, and aggro. I would replace them with two point-blank ae stuns.<br>
<br>
It's hard as hell to channel anything with three things beating on you simultaneously. The color series gives you those precious moments to more-reliably cast individual mezzes or an aoe - whichever you prefer.<br>
<br>
You say the warrior was not taunting ... well, if you land tash, mez, slow, listless and insipid on a mob it would be a challenge even for the SK to grab aggro. It also takes time for 2-3 taunts to cycle (that's what would be required to overcome that much aggro, if not more). DL is all about quick kills.<br>
<br>
That's why you should drop your dedicated buff slot (haste/clarity) and keep root memmed. That will keep the mob hitting the warrior (and the SK if he stands too close) and well away from you. <br>
<br>
I would not bother with mana sieve. The mob will be dead long before you make it go OOM, especially since you won't get a mana dot until 56. I only use it when fighting gating/complete-healing mobs that cannot be stunned.<br>
<br>
FYI my normal xping lineup looks something like this:<br>
<br>
Tash<br>
Single mez<br>
AE mez/charm (depends)<br>
Slow/buffs (swap)<br>
color stun 1<br>
color stun 2<br>
Theft of Thought (trust me you'll love this spell  )<br>
Root <br>
